---
description: Production checks for Android and App Store readiness
globs: ["**/*.{ts,tsx,js,jsx,json,yml,yaml,xml,plist,gradle}"]
alwaysApply: true
---

Prepare the app for production quality on Android and App Store from a code perspective.

Focus areas:
- broken buttons
- broken navigation
- missing routes
- crashes
- undefined values
- missing imports
- invalid event handlers
- production error handling
- loading reliability
- empty-state reliability
- defensive checks for null/undefined
- safe async handling
- stable media and realtime flow
- stable auth/session flow if present
- stable API call handling if present

Allowed:
- add guards
- add try/catch
- add minimal fallback logic
- add missing route files
- connect existing actions
- fix production-breaking issues
- improve code stability

Strictly forbidden:
- do not restyle the app
- do not redesign screens
- do not alter UI hierarchy
- do not change layout
- do not change branding
- do not modernize visuals
- do not swap infrastructure providers
- do not touch protected production infrastructure unless explicitly requested

Default behavior:
prioritize release stability and functional completeness without UI changes.
